Note:
JSON SCHEMA - Draft 2020-12 Parse / Serialize / Validate Facade (Tier 1)

This module is the user-facing surface for JSON Schema. It wraps the
underlying typed AST in json_schema_ast.runa (kept separate for layering
hygiene) with two top-level operations:

  json_schema_parse(json_text)        -> SchemaNode (generic AST)
  json_schema_serialize(schema)       -> JSON text

Validation is exposed by json_schema_ast.runa as

  json_schema_validate(schema, value) -> Integer

which implements Draft 2020-12 validation against the typed AST.

Supported JSON Schema Draft 2020-12 keywords (parse + validate):
  CORE
    type, properties, required, items, additionalProperties, enum,
    const, $defs, $ref, allOf, anyOf, oneOf, not, if/then/else,
    contains, prefixItems, dependentSchemas

  STRING
    minLength, maxLength, pattern, format

  NUMBER
    minimum, maximum, exclusiveMinimum, exclusiveMaximum, multipleOf

  ARRAY
    minItems, maxItems, uniqueItems, contains, prefixItems

  OBJECT
    minProperties, maxProperties, dependentRequired

Format keywords accepted (annotation only unless higher-layer format
registries are wired):
  date, time, date-time, duration, email, idn-email, hostname,
  idn-hostname, ipv4, ipv6, uri, uri-reference, iri, uri-template,
  json-pointer, relative-json-pointer, regex, uuid

Internal JSON parser is intentionally embedded so this module is
self-contained. It accepts UTF-8 JSON text per RFC 8259 and produces a
ConfigValue (CV_*) tree via the Config module, then walks that tree to
build the generic Schema AST defined in schema.runa.

References:
  - JSON Schema Core 2020-12        https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-bhutton-json-schema/01/
  - JSON Schema Validation 2020-12  https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-bhutton-json-schema-validation/01/
  - RFC 8259 (JSON)                 https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc8259
  - RFC 6901 (JSON Pointer)         https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc6901
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dict
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/string_builder.runa" as SB
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/char_core.runa" as Char
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/config/config.runa" as Cfg
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/schema/schema.runa" as Schema

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Note: Internal parser-state record (32 bytes):
Note:   offset  0 : text pointer
Note:   offset  8 : length
Note:   offset 16 : position
Note:   offset 24 : ok flag (1 = no error, 0 = error)
Let PSTATE_SIZE be 32

Note: ============================================================================
Note: JSON LEXER + PARSER (text -> ConfigValue)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate parser state for a JSON text input.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 32 bytes, store the text pointer, length, position 0, ok=1.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pstate_create" takes text as Integer returns Integer:
    Let s be proc allocate from Layout with PSTATE_SIZE
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 0, text
    Let length be 0
    If text is not equal to 0:
        Set length to proc string_length from StringCore with text
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 8, length
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 24, 1
    Return s
End Process

@Reasoning
Skip whitespace (per RFC 8259 sec.2: space, tab, LF, CR).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Advance position while the byte is one of those four whitespace codes.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(k) where k is whitespace span.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Modifies state.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pstate_skip_ws" takes state as Integer returns Integer:
    Let text be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 0
    Let length be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 8
    Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
    While pos is less than length:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
        Let is_ws be 0
        If ch is equal to 32:
            Set is_ws to 1
        End If
        If ch is equal to 9:
            Set is_ws to 1
        End If
        If ch is equal to 10:
            Set is_ws to 1
        End If
        If ch is equal to 13:
            Set is_ws to 1
        End If
        If is_ws is equal to 0:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 16, pos
            Return 1
        End If
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End While
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 16, pos
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Peek the next byte without advancing.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Return text[pos] or -1 at EOF.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns -1 at EOF.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pstate_peek" takes state as Integer returns Integer:
    Let length be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 8
    Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
    If pos is greater than or equal to length:
        Return 0 minus 1
    End If
    Let text be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 0
    Return proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
End Process

@Reasoning
Advance one byte, returning the byte consumed.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load text[pos], pos += 1.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns -1 if at EOF (no advance).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pstate_consume" takes state as Integer returns Integer:
    Let length be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 8
    Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
    If pos is greater than or equal to length:
        Return 0 minus 1
    End If
    Let text be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 0
    Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 16, pos plus 1
    Return ch
End Process

@Reasoning
Mark parser state as failed.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Store 0 in ok-slot.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pstate_fail" takes state as Integer returns Integer:
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 24, 0
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Return 1 if parser state is still ok.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Return state[24].
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pstate_ok" takes state as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 24
End Process

@Reasoning
Try to consume a literal string at the current position. Returns 1 if
matched (position advances), 0 otherwise (position unchanged).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Compare byte by byte; if any byte differs or runs out, restore pos.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|literal|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pstate_consume_literal" takes state as Integer, literal as Integer returns Integer:
    Let length be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 8
    Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
    Let text be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 0
    Let llen be proc string_length from StringCore with literal
    If (pos plus llen) is greater than length:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than llen:
        Let a be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos plus i
        Let b be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with literal, i
        If a is not equal to b:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 16, pos plus llen
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Parse a JSON string literal (RFC 8259 sec.7). The opening quote has not
been consumed when this function is called.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Verify the next byte is '"'. Allocate a StringBuilder. Walk until the
closing '"' is found, decoding escape sequences:
  \\ -> backslash, \" -> quote, \/ -> slash, \b -> 0x08, \f -> 0x0c,
  \n -> 0x0a, \r -> 0x0d, \t -> 0x09, \uXXXX -> 1-3 byte UTF-8.
Return the built string (caller owns).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on malformed escape or unterminated string.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pstate_parse_string" takes state as Integer returns Integer:
    Let opener be proc pstate_consume with state
    If opener is not equal to 34:
        proc pstate_fail with state
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
    If sb is equal to 0:
        proc pstate_fail with state
        Return 0
    End If
    Let length be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 8
    Let done be 0
    While done is equal to 0:
        Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
        If pos is greater than or equal to length:
            proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
            proc pstate_fail with state
            Return 0
        End If
        Let ch be proc pstate_consume with state
        If ch is equal to 34:
            Set done to 1
        Otherwise:
            If ch is equal to 92:
                Let esc be proc pstate_consume with state
                If esc is equal to 34:
                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 34
                Otherwise:
                    If esc is equal to 92:
                        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 92
                    Otherwise:
                        If esc is equal to 47:
                            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 47
                        Otherwise:
                            If esc is equal to 98:
                                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 8
                            Otherwise:
                                If esc is equal to 102:
                                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 12
                                Otherwise:
                                    If esc is equal to 110:
                                        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
                                    Otherwise:
                                        If esc is equal to 114:
                                            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 13
                                        Otherwise:
                                            If esc is equal to 116:
                                                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 9
                                            Otherwise:
                                                If esc is equal to 117:
                                                    Let cp be proc pstate_parse_unicode_4hex with state
                                                    If cp is less than 0:
                                                        proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
                                                        proc pstate_fail with state
                                                        Return 0
                                                    End If
                                                    proc append_utf8 with sb, cp
                                                Otherwise:
                                                    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
                                                    proc pstate_fail with state
                                                    Return 0
                                                End If
                                            End If
                                        End If
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            Otherwise:
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, ch
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Let out be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with sb
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
    Return out
End Process

@Reasoning
Parse exactly four hex digits and return the resulting code point.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Read four bytes; convert each via Char.hex_digit_value; combine.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns -1 on invalid hex.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pstate_parse_unicode_4hex" takes state as Integer returns Integer:
    Let cp be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than 4:
        Let ch be proc pstate_consume with state
        If ch is less than 0:
            Return 0 minus 1
        End If
        Let dv be proc hex_digit_value from Char with ch
        If dv is less than 0:
            Return 0 minus 1
        End If
        Set cp to (cp multiplied by 16) plus dv
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return cp
End Process

@Reasoning
Append a Unicode code point as 1-3 byte UTF-8 to a StringBuilder. Code
points outside BMP (>0xFFFF) would require surrogate-pair handling
beyond the scope of \uXXXX; this implementation accepts only the BMP
range that fits in 4 hex digits.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Branch on cp size: <0x80 -> 1 byte; <0x800 -> 2 bytes; <=0xFFFF -> 3
bytes. Standard UTF-8 encoding.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal. Caller has validated cp >= 0.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "append_utf8" takes sb as Integer, cp as Integer returns Integer:
    If cp is less than 128:
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, cp
        Return 1
    End If
    If cp is less than 2048:
        Let b0 be 192 plus (cp divided by 64)
        Let b1 be 128 plus (cp minus ((cp divided by 64) multiplied by 64))
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, b0
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, b1
        Return 1
    End If
    Let hi be cp divided by 4096
    Let mid be (cp divided by 64) minus (hi multiplied by 64)
    Let lo be cp minus ((cp divided by 64) multiplied by 64)
    Let bb0 be 224 plus hi
    Let bb1 be 128 plus mid
    Let bb2 be 128 plus lo
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, bb0
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, bb1
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, bb2
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Parse a JSON number (integer or float). RFC 8259 sec.6 permits a leading
minus, an integer part (no leading zero except for 0 itself), an
optional fractional part, and an optional exponent.

Number representation policy:
  - If the number has no '.' and no 'e'/'E', produce a CV_INTEGER.
  - Otherwise produce a CV_STRING containing the original text. Float
    parsing requires Float128 support; preserving the original text
    keeps round-trip fidelity intact until the schema layer adds a
    Float ConfigValue constructor.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Mark start; advance through optional sign, digits, optional fraction,
optional exponent. Detect whether '.' or 'e/E' appeared. Substring the
span. Integer path: call string_to_integer. Otherwise return CV_STRING.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|num|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on parse failure (and marks state failed).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pstate_parse_number" takes state as Integer returns Integer:
    Let length be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 8
    Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
    Let text be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 0
    Let start be pos
    Let is_float be 0

    Let ch1 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
    If ch1 is equal to 45:
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End If
    While pos is less than length:
        Let c be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
        Let isd be proc is_digit from Char with c
        If isd is equal to 0:
            Set pos to length plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
        End If
    End While
    Set pos to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
    If ch1 is equal to 45:
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End If
    While pos is less than length:
        Let cc be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
        Let isd2 be proc is_digit from Char with cc
        If isd2 is equal to 0:
            Set pos to 0 minus 1
        Otherwise:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
        End If
        If pos is equal to (0 minus 1):
            Set pos to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            Set pos to length
        End If
    End While

    Set pos to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
    If ch1 is equal to 45:
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End If
    Let in_integer be 1
    While in_integer is equal to 1:
        If pos is greater than or equal to length:
            Set in_integer to 0
        Otherwise:
            Let cd be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
            Let isdig be proc is_digit from Char with cd
            If isdig is equal to 1:
                Set pos to pos plus 1
            Otherwise:
                Set in_integer to 0
            End If
        End If
    End While

    If pos is less than length:
        Let dot_ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
        If dot_ch is equal to 46:
            Set is_float to 1
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            While pos is less than length:
                Let cf be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
                Let isdf be proc is_digit from Char with cf
                If isdf is equal to 1:
                    Set pos to pos plus 1
                Otherwise:
                    Set pos to length plus 1
                End If
            End While
            Set pos to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
            If ch1 is equal to 45:
                Set pos to pos plus 1
            End If
            Let scan_intpart be 1
            While scan_intpart is equal to 1:
                If pos is greater than or equal to length:
                    Set scan_intpart to 0
                Otherwise:
                    Let cd2 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
                    Let isdig2 be proc is_digit from Char with cd2
                    If isdig2 is equal to 1:
                        Set pos to pos plus 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Set scan_intpart to 0
                    End If
                End If
            End While
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            While pos is less than length:
                Let cf2 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
                Let isdf2 be proc is_digit from Char with cf2
                If isdf2 is equal to 1:
                    Set pos to pos plus 1
                Otherwise:
                    Set pos to length plus 1
                End If
            End While
            Set pos to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
            If ch1 is equal to 45:
                Set pos to pos plus 1
            End If
            Let scan2 be 1
            While scan2 is equal to 1:
                If pos is greater than or equal to length:
                    Set scan2 to 0
                Otherwise:
                    Let cd3 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
                    Let isdig3 be proc is_digit from Char with cd3
                    If isdig3 is equal to 1:
                        Set pos to pos plus 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Set scan2 to 0
                    End If
                End If
            End While
            If pos is less than length:
                Let dot2 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
                If dot2 is equal to 46:
                    Set pos to pos plus 1
                    Let frac be 1
                    While frac is equal to 1:
                        If pos is greater than or equal to length:
                            Set frac to 0
                        Otherwise:
                            Let cf3 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
                            Let isdf3 be proc is_digit from Char with cf3
                            If isdf3 is equal to 1:
                                Set pos to pos plus 1
                            Otherwise:
                                Set frac to 0
                            End If
                        End If
                    End While
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If

    If pos is less than length:
        Let ec be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
        If ec is equal to 101:
            Set is_float to 1
        End If
        If ec is equal to 69:
            Set is_float to 1
        End If
        If is_float is equal to 1:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            If pos is less than length:
                Let sign be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
                If sign is equal to 43:
                    Set pos to pos plus 1
                End If
                If sign is equal to 45:
                    Set pos to pos plus 1
                End If
            End If
            Let exp_scan be 1
            While exp_scan is equal to 1:
                If pos is greater than or equal to length:
                    Set exp_scan to 0
                Otherwise:
                    Let cx be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
                    Let isdx be proc is_digit from Char with cx
                    If isdx is equal to 1:
                        Set pos to pos plus 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Set exp_scan to 0
                    End If
                End If
            End While
        End If
    End If

    Let span_len be pos minus start
    If span_len is less than 1:
        proc pstate_fail with state
        Return 0
    End If
    Let span be proc string_substring from StringPrim with text, start, span_len
    If span is equal to 0:
        proc pstate_fail with state
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 16, pos
    If is_float is equal to 1:
        Let cv be proc config_value_string from Cfg with span
        proc deallocate from Layout with span
        Return cv
    End If
    Let iv be proc string_to_integer from StringPrim with span
    proc deallocate from Layout with span
    Return proc config_value_integer from Cfg with iv
End Process

@Reasoning
Parse a JSON value at the current position into a ConfigValue.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Skip whitespace. Switch on the next byte:
  '"' -> string ; '{' -> object ; '[' -> array ;
  't' -> true   ; 'f' -> false  ; 'n' -> null  ;
  '-' or digit -> number.
Otherwise fail.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on parse failure (sets state.ok = 0).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pstate_parse_value" takes state as Integer returns Integer:
    proc pstate_skip_ws with state
    Let ch be proc pstate_peek with state
    If ch is less than 0:
        proc pstate_fail with state
        Return 0
    End If
    If ch is equal to 34:
        Let s be proc pstate_parse_string with state
        If s is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let cv be proc config_value_string from Cfg with s
        proc deallocate from Layout with s
        Return cv
    End If
    If ch is equal to 123:
        Return proc pstate_parse_object with state
    End If
    If ch is equal to 91:
        Return proc pstate_parse_array with state
    End If
    If ch is equal to 116:
        Let m be proc pstate_consume_literal with state, "true"
        If m is equal to 0:
            proc pstate_fail with state
            Return 0
        End If
        Return proc config_value_bool from Cfg with 1
    End If
    If ch is equal to 102:
        Let m2 be proc pstate_consume_literal with state, "false"
        If m2 is equal to 0:
            proc pstate_fail with state
            Return 0
        End If
        Return proc config_value_bool from Cfg with 0
    End If
    If ch is equal to 110:
        Let m3 be proc pstate_consume_literal with state, "null"
        If m3 is equal to 0:
            proc pstate_fail with state
            Return 0
        End If
        Return proc config_value_null from Cfg
    End If
    Let isdig be proc is_digit from Char with ch
    If isdig is equal to 1:
        Return proc pstate_parse_number with state
    End If
    If ch is equal to 45:
        Return proc pstate_parse_number with state
    End If
    proc pstate_fail with state
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Parse a JSON object: { "key" : value (, "key" : value)* }.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Consume '{'. Loop: skip ws; if '}', done. Otherwise parse string key,
expect ':', parse value, set in dict. Then expect ',' or '}'.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over total object text. Space: O(k) for k entries.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on parse failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pstate_parse_object" takes state as Integer returns Integer:
    Let opener be proc pstate_consume with state
    If opener is not equal to 123:
        proc pstate_fail with state
        Return 0
    End If
    Let dict be proc create from Dict
    If dict is equal to 0:
        proc pstate_fail with state
        Return 0
    End If
    proc pstate_skip_ws with state
    Let next_ch be proc pstate_peek with state
    If next_ch is equal to 125:
        proc pstate_consume with state
        Return proc config_value_map from Cfg with dict
    End If
    Let going be 1
    While going is equal to 1:
        proc pstate_skip_ws with state
        Let key be proc pstate_parse_string with state
        If key is equal to 0:
            proc destroy from Dict with dict
            Return 0
        End If
        proc pstate_skip_ws with state
        Let colon be proc pstate_consume with state
        If colon is not equal to 58:
            proc deallocate from Layout with key
            proc destroy from Dict with dict
            proc pstate_fail with state
            Return 0
        End If
        Let val be proc pstate_parse_value with state
        If val is equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with key
            proc destroy from Dict with dict
            Return 0
        End If
        proc set from Dict with dict, key, val
        proc deallocate from Layout with key
        proc pstate_skip_ws with state
        Let after be proc pstate_consume with state
        If after is equal to 125:
            Set going to 0
        Otherwise:
            If after is equal to 44:
                Set going to 1
            Otherwise:
                proc destroy from Dict with dict
                proc pstate_fail with state
                Return 0
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return proc config_value_map from Cfg with dict
End Process

@Reasoning
Parse a JSON array.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Consume '['. Loop: skip ws; if ']', done. Else parse value, push. Expect
',' or ']'.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over array text. Space: O(k).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on parse failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pstate_parse_array" takes state as Integer returns Integer:
    Let opener be proc pstate_consume with state
    If opener is not equal to 91:
        proc pstate_fail with state
        Return 0
    End If
    Let lst be proc list_create from List
    If lst is equal to 0:
        proc pstate_fail with state
        Return 0
    End If
    proc pstate_skip_ws with state
    Let next_ch be proc pstate_peek with state
    If next_ch is equal to 93:
        proc pstate_consume with state
        Return proc config_value_list from Cfg with lst
    End If
    Let going be 1
    While going is equal to 1:
        proc pstate_skip_ws with state
        Let elem be proc pstate_parse_value with state
        If elem is equal to 0:
            proc list_destroy from List with lst
            Return 0
        End If
        proc list_push from List with lst, elem
        proc pstate_skip_ws with state
        Let after be proc pstate_consume with state
        If after is equal to 93:
            Set going to 0
        Otherwise:
            If after is equal to 44:
                Set going to 1
            Otherwise:
                proc list_destroy from List with lst
                proc pstate_fail with state
                Return 0
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return proc config_value_list from Cfg with lst
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: JSON TEXT -> CV_TREE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Parse a complete JSON document into a ConfigValue tree.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Create parser state, parse one value, skip trailing whitespace, verify
EOF. Free state. On failure destroy partial tree.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on parse failure or null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "json_to_config_value" takes json_text as Integer returns Integer:
    If json_text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let state be proc pstate_create with json_text
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let value be proc pstate_parse_value with state
    proc pstate_skip_ws with state
    Let ok be proc pstate_ok with state
    Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
    Let length be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 8
    proc deallocate from Layout with state
    If ok is equal to 0:
        If value is not equal to 0:
            proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with value
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    If pos is not equal to length:
        If value is not equal to 0:
            proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with value
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    Return value
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CV_TREE -> Schema AST  (interprets a JSON Schema)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Translate a JSON-Schema CV_MAP into a generic SchemaNode. The top-level
schema may be a Boolean true (always-valid: SCHEMA_ANY) or a Boolean
false (never-valid: SCHEMA_UNION with no variants), or an Object with
keywords.

Recognized "type" values map to SCHEMA_* kinds:
  "string" -> STRING ; "integer" -> INTEGER ; "number" -> FLOAT ;
  "boolean" -> BOOLEAN ; "null" -> NULL ; "object" -> OBJECT ;
  "array" -> ARRAY ; or array-of-type-names -> UNION over those.

Per-keyword application:
  - "properties"+"required" -> OBJECT with required ObjectFields.
  - "items" -> ARRAY whose item schema is the recursive translation.
  - "enum" -> ENUM with the string entries.
  - "minLength" / "maxLength" / "pattern" / "format" -> string
    constraints on the result.
  - "minimum" / "maximum" / "multipleOf" -> integer constraints.
  - "anyOf"/"oneOf" -> UNION over the variants. oneOf is recorded as a
    titled union ("oneOf"); XOR semantics are evaluated at validation
    time by the json_schema_ast validator.
  - "$ref" -> SCHEMA_REFERENCE.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Top-level: if value is CV_BOOL, dispatch trivially. Else cast to CV_MAP
and look up "type" / "$ref" / etc. Build a SchemaNode of the right kind
and decorate it. Recurse into nested "properties" / "items" / "anyOf" /
"oneOf".
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over schema document.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input or unrecognized structure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "cv_to_schema" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let vk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with value
    If vk is equal to 4:
        Let b be proc config_value_as_bool from Cfg with value
        If b is equal to 1:
            Return proc schema_create_any from Schema
        End If
        Return proc schema_create_union from Schema
    End If
    If vk is not equal to 6:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let dict be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with value

    Let ref_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "$ref"
    If ref_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let rk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with ref_cv
        If rk is equal to 1:
            Let rstr be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with ref_cv
            Return proc schema_create_reference from Schema with rstr
        End If
    End If

    Let const_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "const"
    If const_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let const_copy be proc cv_deep_copy with const_cv
        If const_copy is not equal to 0:
            Return proc schema_create_const from Schema with const_copy
        End If
    End If

    Let enum_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "enum"
    If enum_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let ek be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with enum_cv
        If ek is equal to 5:
            Let enode be proc schema_create_enum from Schema
            Let elst be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with enum_cv
            Let ec be proc list_length from List with elst
            Let ei be 0
            While ei is less than ec:
                Let elem be proc list_get from List with elst, ei
                Let elk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with elem
                If elk is equal to 1:
                    Let esv be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with elem
                    proc schema_enum_add_value from Schema with enode, esv
                End If
                Set ei to ei plus 1
            End While
            Return enode
        End If
    End If

    Let allof_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "allOf"
    If allof_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let allk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with allof_cv
        If allk is equal to 5:
            Let allnode be proc schema_create_all_of from Schema
            Let all_lst be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with allof_cv
            Let all_c be proc list_length from List with all_lst
            Let all_i be 0
            While all_i is less than all_c:
                Let all_var be proc list_get from List with all_lst, all_i
                Let all_sub be proc cv_to_schema with all_var
                If all_sub is not equal to 0:
                    proc schema_composite_add_subschema from Schema with allnode, all_sub
                End If
                Set all_i to all_i plus 1
            End While
            Note: Attach root-level $defs if present so nested $ref nodes resolve.
            Let allof_defs_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "$defs"
            If allof_defs_cv is not equal to 0:
                proc attach_defs_to_schema with allnode, allof_defs_cv
            End If
            Return allnode
        End If
    End If

    Let not_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "not"
    If not_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let nk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with not_cv
        If nk is equal to 6:
            Let inner be proc cv_to_schema with not_cv
            If inner is not equal to 0:
                Let not_node be proc schema_compose from Schema with inner, 0, 3
                Note: Attach root-level $defs if present.
                Let not_defs_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "$defs"
                If not_defs_cv is not equal to 0:
                    proc attach_defs_to_schema with not_node, not_defs_cv
                End If
                Return not_node
            End If
        End If
        If nk is equal to 4:
            Let nb be proc config_value_as_bool from Cfg with not_cv
            Let bool_inner be 0
            If nb is equal to 1:
                Set bool_inner to proc schema_create_any from Schema
            Otherwise:
                Set bool_inner to proc schema_create_union from Schema
            End If
            If bool_inner is not equal to 0:
                Let not_bool_node be proc schema_compose from Schema with bool_inner, 0, 3
                Return not_bool_node
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let anyof_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "anyOf"
    If anyof_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let ak be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with anyof_cv
        If ak is equal to 5:
            Let unode be proc schema_create_union from Schema
            Let alst be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with anyof_cv
            Let ac be proc list_length from List with alst
            Let ai be 0
            While ai is less than ac:
                Let variant be proc list_get from List with alst, ai
                Let vs be proc cv_to_schema with variant
                If vs is not equal to 0:
                    proc schema_union_add_variant from Schema with unode, vs
                End If
                Set ai to ai plus 1
            End While
            Let anyof_defs_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "$defs"
            If anyof_defs_cv is not equal to 0:
                proc attach_defs_to_schema with unode, anyof_defs_cv
            End If
            Return unode
        End If
    End If

    Let oneof_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "oneOf"
    If oneof_cv is not equal to 0:
        Let ok2 be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with oneof_cv
        If ok2 is equal to 5:
            Let onode be proc schema_create_one_of from Schema
            proc schema_set_title from Schema with onode, "oneOf"
            Let olst be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with oneof_cv
            Let oc be proc list_length from List with olst
            Let oi be 0
            While oi is less than oc:
                Let ovar be proc list_get from List with olst, oi
                Let os be proc cv_to_schema with ovar
                If os is not equal to 0:
                    proc schema_composite_add_subschema from Schema with onode, os
                End If
                Set oi to oi plus 1
            End While
            Let oneof_defs_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "$defs"
            If oneof_defs_cv is not equal to 0:
                proc attach_defs_to_schema with onode, oneof_defs_cv
            End If
            Return onode
        End If
    End If

    Let type_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "type"
    If type_cv is equal to 0:
        Note: No type keyword - still honor numeric exclusiveMin/Max,
        Note: $defs / additionalProperties on a bare object schema. The
        Note: simplest fallback that handles the most common JSON Schema
        Note: pattern ({"exclusiveMinimum": 0}) is to scan for those
        Note: keywords and produce an integer schema if present.
        Let bare_ex_min be proc get from Dict with dict, "exclusiveMinimum"
        Let bare_ex_max be proc get from Dict with dict, "exclusiveMaximum"
        If bare_ex_min is not equal to 0:
            Let bare_node be proc build_typed_schema with "integer", dict
            Return bare_node
        End If
        If bare_ex_max is not equal to 0:
            Let bare_node2 be proc build_typed_schema with "integer", dict
            Return bare_node2
        End If
        Let any_node be proc schema_create_any from Schema
        Let any_defs_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "$defs"
        If any_defs_cv is not equal to 0:
            proc attach_defs_to_schema with any_node, any_defs_cv
        End If
        Return any_node
    End If
    Let tk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with type_cv
    If tk is equal to 1:
        Let tname be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with type_cv
        Let typed_node be proc build_typed_schema with tname, dict
        Let typed_defs_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "$defs"
        If typed_defs_cv is not equal to 0:
            proc attach_defs_to_schema with typed_node, typed_defs_cv
        End If
        Return typed_node
    End If
    If tk is equal to 5:
        Let union_node be proc schema_create_union from Schema
        Let tlst be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with type_cv
        Let tc be proc list_length from List with tlst
        Let ti be 0
        While ti is less than tc:
            Let tv be proc list_get from List with tlst, ti
            Let tvk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with tv
            If tvk is equal to 1:
                Let nm be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with tv
                Let variant be proc build_typed_schema with nm, dict
                If variant is not equal to 0:
                    proc schema_union_add_variant from Schema with union_node, variant
                End If
            End If
            Set ti to ti plus 1
        End While
        Let typu_defs_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "$defs"
        If typu_defs_cv is not equal to 0:
            proc attach_defs_to_schema with union_node, typu_defs_cv
        End If
        Return union_node
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Read a JSON Schema $defs dictionary (CV_MAP) and populate the supplied
schema's definitions registry. Each (name, sub-schema) entry is
translated via cv_to_schema and stored under the same name.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Verify the input is a CV_MAP. Iterate keys; translate each value with
cv_to_schema; store with schema_add_definition.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over definitions. Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal. Silently skips non-map inputs and entries whose values are
not parseable as schemas.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attach_defs_to_schema" takes schema as Integer, defs_cv as Integer returns Integer:
    If schema is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If defs_cv is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let dk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with defs_cv
    If dk is not equal to 6:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let defs_dict be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with defs_cv
    If defs_dict is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let names be proc keys from Dict with defs_dict
    If names is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let n_count be proc list_length from List with names
    Let n_i be 0
    While n_i is less than n_count:
        Let nm be proc list_get from List with names, n_i
        If nm is not equal to 0:
            Let nv be proc get from Dict with defs_dict, nm
            Let nsch be proc cv_to_schema with nv
            If nsch is not equal to 0:
                proc schema_add_definition from Schema with schema, nm, nsch
            End If
        End If
        Set n_i to n_i plus 1
    End While
    proc list_destroy from List with names
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Deep-copy a ConfigValue tree so the result has independent ownership
from the source. Used by SCHEMA_CONST so the schema can own its const
value after the JSON parse tree is destroyed.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Switch on CV_* kind and reconstruct an isomorphic tree. CV_STRING
duplicates the string via config_value_string (which duplicates).
CV_LIST and CV_MAP recurse through their entries.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over the source. Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input or allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "cv_deep_copy" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let k be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with value
    If k is equal to 0:
        Return proc config_value_null from Cfg
    End If
    If k is equal to 1:
        Let s be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with value
        Return proc config_value_string from Cfg with s
    End If
    If k is equal to 2:
        Let iv be proc config_value_as_integer from Cfg with value
        Return proc config_value_integer from Cfg with iv
    End If
    If k is equal to 3:
        Let fs be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with value
        Return proc config_value_string from Cfg with fs
    End If
    If k is equal to 4:
        Let bv be proc config_value_as_bool from Cfg with value
        Return proc config_value_bool from Cfg with bv
    End If
    If k is equal to 5:
        Let new_list be proc list_create from List
        Let src_list be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with value
        If src_list is not equal to 0:
            Let len be proc list_length from List with src_list
            Let li be 0
            While li is less than len:
                Let elem be proc list_get from List with src_list, li
                Let elem_copy be proc cv_deep_copy with elem
                If elem_copy is not equal to 0:
                    proc list_push from List with new_list, elem_copy
                End If
                Set li to li plus 1
            End While
        End If
        Return proc config_value_list from Cfg with new_list
    End If
    If k is equal to 6:
        Let new_map be proc create from Dict
        Let src_map be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with value
        If src_map is not equal to 0:
            Let mkeys be proc keys from Dict with src_map
            If mkeys is not equal to 0:
                Let mn be proc list_length from List with mkeys
                Let mi be 0
                While mi is less than mn:
                    Let mk be proc list_get from List with mkeys, mi
                    If mk is not equal to 0:
                        Let mv be proc get from Dict with src_map, mk
                        Let mv_copy be proc cv_deep_copy with mv
                        If mv_copy is not equal to 0:
                            Note: Dict.set duplicates the key internally, so we
                            Note: pass the original; the source map retains
                            Note: ownership of its own keys.
                            proc set from Dict with new_map, mk, mv_copy
                        End If
                    End If
                    Set mi to mi plus 1
                End While
                proc list_destroy from List with mkeys
            End If
        End If
        Return proc config_value_map from Cfg with new_map
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Build a SchemaNode for a single type name string, decorating it with the
applicable keyword constraints from the surrounding schema CV_MAP.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Match the type name and dispatch to the corresponding schema constructor.
Then read keyword-specific entries from dict and stamp constraints onto
the constructed node.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over the keywords present.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal. Returns 0 on unknown type.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "build_typed_schema" takes tname as Integer, dict as Integer returns Integer:
    If tname is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let eq_str be proc string_equals from StringCore with tname, "string"
    If eq_str is equal to 1:
        Let mn be 0 minus 1
        Let mx be 0 minus 1
        Let mnv be proc get from Dict with dict, "minLength"
        If mnv is not equal to 0:
            Let mnvk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with mnv
            If mnvk is equal to 2:
                Set mn to proc config_value_as_integer from Cfg with mnv
            End If
        End If
        Let mxv be proc get from Dict with dict, "maxLength"
        If mxv is not equal to 0:
            Let mxvk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with mxv
            If mxvk is equal to 2:
                Set mx to proc config_value_as_integer from Cfg with mxv
            End If
        End If
        Let patv be proc get from Dict with dict, "pattern"
        Let pat be 0
        If patv is not equal to 0:
            Let pvk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with patv
            If pvk is equal to 1:
                Set pat to proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with patv
            End If
        End If
        Let fmtv be proc get from Dict with dict, "format"
        Let fmt be 0
        If fmtv is not equal to 0:
            Let fvk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with fmtv
            If fvk is equal to 1:
                Let fname be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with fmtv
                Set fmt to proc format_name_to_constant with fname
            End If
        End If
        Let sc be proc string_constraints_create from Schema with mn, mx, pat, fmt
        If sc is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return proc schema_create from Schema with 3, sc
    End If
    Let eq_int be proc string_equals from StringCore with tname, "integer"
    If eq_int is equal to 1:
        Let has_min be 0
        Let mnval be 0
        Let has_max be 0
        Let mxval be 0
        Let mof be 0
        Let mnv2 be proc get from Dict with dict, "minimum"
        If mnv2 is not equal to 0:
            Let mvk2 be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with mnv2
            If mvk2 is equal to 2:
                Set has_min to 1
                Set mnval to proc config_value_as_integer from Cfg with mnv2
            End If
        End If
        Let mxv2 be proc get from Dict with dict, "maximum"
        If mxv2 is not equal to 0:
            Let mvk3 be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with mxv2
            If mvk3 is equal to 2:
                Set has_max to 1
                Set mxval to proc config_value_as_integer from Cfg with mxv2
            End If
        End If
        Let mofv be proc get from Dict with dict, "multipleOf"
        If mofv is not equal to 0:
            Let mvkm be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with mofv
            If mvkm is equal to 2:
                Set mof to proc config_value_as_integer from Cfg with mofv
            End If
        End If
        Let ic be proc integer_constraints_create from Schema with has_min, mnval, has_max, mxval, mof
        If ic is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let int_node be proc schema_create from Schema with 4, ic
        If int_node is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let exmin_int_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "exclusiveMinimum"
        If exmin_int_cv is not equal to 0:
            Let exmin_int_k be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with exmin_int_cv
            If exmin_int_k is equal to 2:
                Let exmin_int_v be proc config_value_as_integer from Cfg with exmin_int_cv
                proc schema_set_exclusive_minimum from Schema with int_node, exmin_int_v
            End If
        End If
        Let exmax_int_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "exclusiveMaximum"
        If exmax_int_cv is not equal to 0:
            Let exmax_int_k be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with exmax_int_cv
            If exmax_int_k is equal to 2:
                Let exmax_int_v be proc config_value_as_integer from Cfg with exmax_int_cv
                proc schema_set_exclusive_maximum from Schema with int_node, exmax_int_v
            End If
        End If
        Return int_node
    End If
    Let eq_num be proc string_equals from StringCore with tname, "number"
    If eq_num is equal to 1:
        Let num_node be proc schema_create_float_any from Schema
        If num_node is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let exmin_num_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "exclusiveMinimum"
        If exmin_num_cv is not equal to 0:
            Let exmin_num_k be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with exmin_num_cv
            If exmin_num_k is equal to 2:
                Let exmin_num_v be proc config_value_as_integer from Cfg with exmin_num_cv
                proc schema_set_exclusive_minimum from Schema with num_node, exmin_num_v
            End If
        End If
        Let exmax_num_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "exclusiveMaximum"
        If exmax_num_cv is not equal to 0:
            Let exmax_num_k be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with exmax_num_cv
            If exmax_num_k is equal to 2:
                Let exmax_num_v be proc config_value_as_integer from Cfg with exmax_num_cv
                proc schema_set_exclusive_maximum from Schema with num_node, exmax_num_v
            End If
        End If
        Return num_node
    End If
    Let eq_bool be proc string_equals from StringCore with tname, "boolean"
    If eq_bool is equal to 1:
        Return proc schema_create_boolean from Schema
    End If
    Let eq_null be proc string_equals from StringCore with tname, "null"
    If eq_null is equal to 1:
        Return proc schema_create_null from Schema
    End If
    Let eq_arr be proc string_equals from StringCore with tname, "array"
    If eq_arr is equal to 1:
        Let arr_min be 0 minus 1
        Let arr_max be 0 minus 1
        Let arr_unique be 0
        Let min_items_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "minItems"
        If min_items_cv is not equal to 0:
            Let min_items_k be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with min_items_cv
            If min_items_k is equal to 2:
                Set arr_min to proc config_value_as_integer from Cfg with min_items_cv
            End If
        End If
        Let max_items_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "maxItems"
        If max_items_cv is not equal to 0:
            Let max_items_k be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with max_items_cv
            If max_items_k is equal to 2:
                Set arr_max to proc config_value_as_integer from Cfg with max_items_cv
            End If
        End If
        Let unique_items_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "uniqueItems"
        If unique_items_cv is not equal to 0:
            Let unique_items_k be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with unique_items_cv
            If unique_items_k is equal to 4:
                Set arr_unique to proc config_value_as_bool from Cfg with unique_items_cv
            End If
        End If
        Let items_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "items"
        Let arr_node be 0
        If items_cv is equal to 0:
            Let any_item be proc schema_create_any from Schema
            Set arr_node to proc schema_create_array from Schema with any_item, arr_min, arr_max, arr_unique
        Otherwise:
            Let item_schema be proc cv_to_schema with items_cv
            If item_schema is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            Set arr_node to proc schema_create_array from Schema with item_schema, arr_min, arr_max, arr_unique
        End If
        If arr_node is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let prefix_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "prefixItems"
        If prefix_cv is not equal to 0:
            Let prefix_k be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with prefix_cv
            If prefix_k is equal to 5:
                Let prefix_lst be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with prefix_cv
                Let prefix_c be proc list_length from List with prefix_lst
                Let prefix_i be 0
                While prefix_i is less than prefix_c:
                    Let prefix_elem be proc list_get from List with prefix_lst, prefix_i
                    Let prefix_sub be proc cv_to_schema with prefix_elem
                    If prefix_sub is not equal to 0:
                        proc schema_array_add_prefix_item from Schema with arr_node, prefix_sub
                    End If
                    Set prefix_i to prefix_i plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If
        Let contains_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "contains"
        If contains_cv is not equal to 0:
            Let contains_k be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with contains_cv
            If contains_k is equal to 6:
                Let contains_sub be proc cv_to_schema with contains_cv
                If contains_sub is not equal to 0:
                    proc schema_array_set_contains from Schema with arr_node, contains_sub
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Return arr_node
    End If
    Let eq_obj be proc string_equals from StringCore with tname, "object"
    If eq_obj is equal to 1:
        Let onode be proc schema_create_object from Schema
        Let props_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "properties"
        Let required_set be proc create from Dict
        Let req_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "required"
        If req_cv is not equal to 0:
            Let rk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with req_cv
            If rk is equal to 5:
                Let rlst be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with req_cv
                Let rc be proc list_length from List with rlst
                Let ri be 0
                While ri is less than rc:
                    Let re be proc list_get from List with rlst, ri
                    Let rek be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with re
                    If rek is equal to 1:
                        Let rs be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with re
                        proc set from Dict with required_set, rs, re
                    End If
                    Set ri to ri plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If
        If props_cv is not equal to 0:
            Let pk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with props_cv
            If pk is equal to 6:
                Let pdict be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with props_cv
                Let pkeys be proc keys from Dict with pdict
                Let pc be proc list_length from List with pkeys
                Let pi be 0
                While pi is less than pc:
                    Let pkey be proc list_get from List with pkeys, pi
                    Let pval be proc get from Dict with pdict, pkey
                    Let psub be proc cv_to_schema with pval
                    If psub is not equal to 0:
                        Let in_req be proc get from Dict with required_set, pkey
                        Let req_flag be 0
                        If in_req is not equal to 0:
                            Set req_flag to 1
                        End If
                        Let fld be proc object_field_create from Schema with pkey, psub, req_flag
                        If fld is not equal to 0:
                            proc schema_object_add_field from Schema with onode, fld
                        End If
                    End If
                    Set pi to pi plus 1
                End While
                proc list_destroy from List with pkeys
            End If
        End If
        proc destroy from Dict with required_set
        Note: additionalProperties: false | true | <schema>.
        Let ap_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "additionalProperties"
        If ap_cv is not equal to 0:
            Let ap_k be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with ap_cv
            If ap_k is equal to 4:
                Let ap_b be proc config_value_as_bool from Cfg with ap_cv
                If ap_b is equal to 0:
                    proc schema_object_set_additional_properties_false from Schema with onode
                End If
            End If
            If ap_k is equal to 6:
                Let ap_sub be proc cv_to_schema with ap_cv
                If ap_sub is not equal to 0:
                    proc schema_object_set_additional_properties_schema from Schema with onode, ap_sub
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Note: dependentRequired: { trigger_key: [ "needed_a", "needed_b" ] }
        Let dr_cv be proc get from Dict with dict, "dependentRequired"
        If dr_cv is not equal to 0:
            Let dr_k be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with dr_cv
            If dr_k is equal to 6:
                Let dr_map be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with dr_cv
                If dr_map is not equal to 0:
                    Let dr_keys be proc keys from Dict with dr_map
                    If dr_keys is not equal to 0:
                        Let dr_count be proc list_length from List with dr_keys
                        Let dr_i be 0
                        While dr_i is less than dr_count:
                            Let dr_key be proc list_get from List with dr_keys, dr_i
                            If dr_key is not equal to 0:
                                Let dr_val be proc get from Dict with dr_map, dr_key
                                Let dr_val_k be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with dr_val
                                If dr_val_k is equal to 5:
                                    Let dr_val_lst be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with dr_val
                                    Let dr_needed_list be proc list_create from List
                                    If dr_needed_list is not equal to 0:
                                        Let dr_vn be proc list_length from List with dr_val_lst
                                        Let dr_vi be 0
                                        While dr_vi is less than dr_vn:
                                            Let dr_name_cv be proc list_get from List with dr_val_lst, dr_vi
                                            Let dr_name_k be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with dr_name_cv
                                            If dr_name_k is equal to 1:
                                                Let dr_name_str be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with dr_name_cv
                                                Let dr_name_dup be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with dr_name_str
                                                If dr_name_dup is not equal to 0:
                                                    proc list_push from List with dr_needed_list, dr_name_dup
                                                End If
                                            End If
                                            Set dr_vi to dr_vi plus 1
                                        End While
                                        proc schema_object_add_dependent_required from Schema with onode, dr_key, dr_needed_list
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                            Set dr_i to dr_i plus 1
                        End While
                        proc list_destroy from List with dr_keys
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Return onode
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Translate a JSON Schema format identifier to the corresponding
SCHEMA.FORMAT_* constant.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Linear string comparison against each recognized format name.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(k) where k is number of format names (constant).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns FORMAT_NONE (0) for unrecognized format strings.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "format_name_to_constant" takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let m1 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "email"
    If m1 is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let m2 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "uri"
    If m2 is equal to 1:
        Return 13
    End If
    Let m3 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "uri-reference"
    If m3 is equal to 1:
        Return 14
    End If
    Let m4 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "uuid"
    If m4 is equal to 1:
        Return 3
    End If
    Let m5 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "date"
    If m5 is equal to 1:
        Return 4
    End If
    Let m6 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "time"
    If m6 is equal to 1:
        Return 5
    End If
    Let m7 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "date-time"
    If m7 is equal to 1:
        Return 6
    End If
    Let m8 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "duration"
    If m8 is equal to 1:
        Return 7
    End If
    Let m9 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "ipv4"
    If m9 is equal to 1:
        Return 8
    End If
    Let m10 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "ipv6"
    If m10 is equal to 1:
        Return 9
    End If
    Let m11 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "hostname"
    If m11 is equal to 1:
        Return 10
    End If
    Let m12 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "regex"
    If m12 is equal to 1:
        Return 11
    End If
    Let m13 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "json-pointer"
    If m13 is equal to 1:
        Return 12
    End If
    Let m14 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "idn-email"
    If m14 is equal to 1:
        Return 15
    End If
    Let m15 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "idn-hostname"
    If m15 is equal to 1:
        Return 16
    End If
    Let m16 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "iri"
    If m16 is equal to 1:
        Return 17
    End If
    Let m17 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "uri-template"
    If m17 is equal to 1:
        Return 18
    End If
    Let m18 be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "relative-json-pointer"
    If m18 is equal to 1:
        Return 19
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TOP-LEVEL API
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Parse a JSON Schema document (UTF-8 text) into a generic SchemaNode.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Parse the text into a ConfigValue, then translate via cv_to_schema. The
intermediate CV tree is destroyed before return.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on parse error or null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "json_schema_parse" takes json_text as Integer returns Integer:
    If json_text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cv be proc json_to_config_value with json_text
    If cv is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let schema be proc cv_to_schema with cv
    proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with cv
    Return schema
End Process

@Reasoning
Serialize a SchemaNode back into JSON-Schema-compatible JSON text.
Round-trip is lossy for keywords that were not represented in the
generic AST (e.g. exclusiveMinimum, additionalProperties), but every
preserved keyword is emitted in canonical form.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Build the JSON output via StringBuilder using a recursive walker that
inspects schema kind:
  OBJECT: { "type": "object", "properties": {...}, "required": [...] }
  ARRAY : { "type": "array", "items": {...} }
  STRING: { "type": "string", "minLength": N, "maxLength": N, "pattern": "..." }
  INTEGER: { "type": "integer", "minimum": N, "maximum": N }
  FLOAT  : { "type": "number" }
  BOOLEAN: { "type": "boolean" }
  NULL   : { "type": "null" }
  ANY    : true
  ENUM   : { "enum": [...] }
  UNION  : title="oneOf" emits { "oneOf": [...] }, else { "anyOf": [...] }
  REFERENCE: { "$ref": "..." }
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over schema. Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input or allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "json_schema_serialize" takes schema as Integer returns Integer:
    If schema is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
    If sb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc emit_schema with sb, schema
    Let out be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with sb
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
    Return out
End Process

@Reasoning
Internal recursive emitter writing a SchemaNode into a StringBuilder.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Switch on kind and write the appropriate JSON object/value, recursing
into children.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "emit_schema" takes sb as Integer, schema as Integer returns Integer:
    If schema is equal to 0:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "true"
        Return 1
    End If
    Let kind be proc schema_kind from Schema with schema
    Let payload be proc schema_payload from Schema with schema
    If kind is equal to 11:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "true"
        Return 1
    End If
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 123
    If kind is equal to 1:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "\"type\":\"object\""
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let count be proc list_length from List with payload
            If count is greater than 0:
                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, ",\"properties\":{"
                Let i be 0
                While i is less than count:
                    Let fld be proc list_get from List with payload, i
                    If fld is not equal to 0:
                        Let nm be proc object_field_name from Schema with fld
                        Let sub be proc object_field_schema from Schema with fld
                        If i is greater than 0:
                            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 44
                        End If
                        proc emit_json_string with sb, nm
                        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 58
                        proc emit_schema with sb, sub
                    End If
                    Set i to i plus 1
                End While
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 125
                Let any_req be 0
                Let j be 0
                While j is less than count:
                    Let fld2 be proc list_get from List with payload, j
                    If fld2 is not equal to 0:
                        Let req be proc object_field_is_required from Schema with fld2
                        If req is equal to 1:
                            Set any_req to 1
                        End If
                    End If
                    Set j to j plus 1
                End While
                If any_req is equal to 1:
                    proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, ",\"required\":["
                    Let k be 0
                    Let first_req be 1
                    While k is less than count:
                        Let fld3 be proc list_get from List with payload, k
                        If fld3 is not equal to 0:
                            Let req2 be proc object_field_is_required from Schema with fld3
                            If req2 is equal to 1:
                                If first_req is equal to 0:
                                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 44
                                End If
                                Set first_req to 0
                                Let nm2 be proc object_field_name from Schema with fld3
                                proc emit_json_string with sb, nm2
                            End If
                        End If
                        Set k to k plus 1
                    End While
                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 93
                End If
            End If
        End If
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 125
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to 2:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":"
        proc emit_schema with sb, payload
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 125
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to 3:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "\"type\":\"string\""
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let mn be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 0
            If mn is greater than or equal to 0:
                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, ",\"minLength\":"
                proc stringbuilder_append_integer from SB with sb, mn
            End If
            Let mx be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 8
            If mx is greater than or equal to 0:
                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, ",\"maxLength\":"
                proc stringbuilder_append_integer from SB with sb, mx
            End If
        End If
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 125
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to 4:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "\"type\":\"integer\""
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let hm be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 0
            If hm is equal to 1:
                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, ",\"minimum\":"
                Let mv be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 8
                proc stringbuilder_append_integer from SB with sb, mv
            End If
            Let hM be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 16
            If hM is equal to 1:
                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, ",\"maximum\":"
                Let Mv be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 24
                proc stringbuilder_append_integer from SB with sb, Mv
            End If
            Let mof be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 32
            If mof is not equal to 0:
                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, ",\"multipleOf\":"
                proc stringbuilder_append_integer from SB with sb, mof
            End If
        End If
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 125
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to 5:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "\"type\":\"number\""
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 125
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to 6:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "\"type\":\"boolean\""
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 125
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to 7:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "\"type\":\"null\""
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 125
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to 8:
        Let title be proc schema_title from Schema with schema
        Let is_one be 0
        If title is not equal to 0:
            Let teq be proc string_equals from StringCore with title, "oneOf"
            If teq is equal to 1:
                Set is_one to 1
            End If
        End If
        If is_one is equal to 1:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "\"oneOf\":["
        Otherwise:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "\"anyOf\":["
        End If
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let vc be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let v_i be 0
            While v_i is less than vc:
                Let variant be proc list_get from List with payload, v_i
                If v_i is greater than 0:
                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 44
                End If
                proc emit_schema with sb, variant
                Set v_i to v_i plus 1
            End While
        End If
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "]}"
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to 9:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "\"$ref\":"
        proc emit_json_string with sb, payload
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 125
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to 10:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "\"enum\":["
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let ec be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let ei be 0
            While ei is less than ec:
                Let val be proc list_get from List with payload, ei
                If ei is greater than 0:
                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 44
                End If
                proc emit_json_string with sb, val
                Set ei to ei plus 1
            End While
        End If
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "]}"
        Return 1
    End If
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 125
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Emit a JSON string literal: opening quote, body with escape encoding,
closing quote.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Write '"'. For each byte: " -> \\\", \\ -> \\\\, control chars 0-31 ->
\\uXXXX, else literal. Write '"'.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal. Assumes byte input is valid UTF-8.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "emit_json_string" takes sb as Integer, s as Integer returns Integer:
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 34
    If s is not equal to 0:
        Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with s
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than length:
            Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with s, i
            If ch is equal to 34:
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 92
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 34
            Otherwise:
                If ch is equal to 92:
                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 92
                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 92
                Otherwise:
                    If ch is equal to 10:
                        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 92
                        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 110
                    Otherwise:
                        If ch is equal to 13:
                            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 92
                            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 114
                        Otherwise:
                            If ch is equal to 9:
                                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 92
                                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 116
                            Otherwise:
                                If ch is less than 32:
                                    proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "\\u00"
                                    Let hi be ch divided by 16
                                    Let lo be ch minus (hi multiplied by 16)
                                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, proc hex_char with hi
                                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, proc hex_char with lo
                                Otherwise:
                                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, ch
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 34
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Hex digit to ASCII character.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
0..9 -> '0'..'9', 10..15 -> 'a'..'f'.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal. Caller passes 0..15.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "hex_char" takes n as Integer returns Integer:
    If n is less than 10:
        Return 48 plus n
    End If
    Return 87 plus n
End Process

Note:
Validation entry points live in json_schema_ast.runa, which owns the
typed JSON-Schema AST and implements the Draft 2020-12 validation
semantics (allOf/oneOf/not/const/format-aware/numeric-bound-aware).
The validator there has the signature

    json_schema_validate(schema, value) -> Integer

so callers should import json_schema_ast directly when validation is
required. This module (the facade) intentionally exposes only the
parser and serializer surface to avoid maintaining two parallel
validator implementations that drift apart.
:End Note
